"**Comparison of Energy and Sustainability Policies: Ranil Wickremesinghe vs. Anura Kumara Dissanayake**\n\n| **Policy Area** | **Ranil Wickremesinghe** | **Anura Kumara Dissanayake** |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Renewable Energy | Encourage investments in renewable energy production, aiming for 70% of power supply from renewable sources by 2030 | Increase renewable energy sources to foster a green economy |\n| Green Energy Hub | Transform Sri Lanka into a Green Energy Hub, enabling energy exports to neighboring countries | No data available |\n| Natural Gas Power Generation | Expect a rise in natural gas power generation | No data available |\n| Reduced Energy Costs | Reduce the cost of energy consumption for citizens | No data available |\n| Emission Trading Scheme | Introduce an emission trading scheme in line with international standards | No data available |\n| Carbon Tax | Introduce a carbon tax to control emissions | No data available |\n| Environmental Sustainability | Implement environmentally friendly procedures across agriculture, industries, and energy sectors | Establish a comprehensive program to empower industries to meet global market standards for fair trade, labor quality, and transparency |\n| Climate Change Mitigation | Adapt to and mitigate the impacts of climate change through a comprehensive five-year action plan | Develop a strategic initiative to address environmental sustainability, climate change challenges, and achieve long-term resilience and skill development in the industrial sector |\n| Sustainable Development | Open doors to innovative job opportunities in sustainable development and technology | Promote international partnerships and investments in sustainable energy projects through Renewable Energy Diplomacy |\n\n**Common Policies:**\n\n* Both candidates emphasize the importance of increasing renewable energy sources and promoting environmental sustainability.\n* Both candidates aim to reduce the country's dependence on oil-based electricity generation.\n\n**Unique or Innovative Policies:**\n\n* Ranil Wickremesinghe:\n\t+ Transforming Sri Lanka into a Green Energy Hub, enabling energy exports to neighboring countries.\n\t+ Introducing a carbon tax to control emissions.\n\t+ Implementing an emission trading scheme in line with international standards.\n* Anura Kumara Dissanayake:\n\t+ Emphasis on transitioning to an energy mix that is least dependent on oil-based electricity generation.\n\t+ Comprehensive approach to addressing environmental sustainability and climate change challenges.\n\t+ Promotion of international partnerships and investments in sustainable energy projects.\n\n**Analysis:**\n\nRanil Wickremesinghe's policies focus on transforming Sri Lanka into a Green Energy Hub, reducing energy costs, and introducing a carbon tax to control emissions. His approach is more focused on specific targets and timelines, such as achieving 70% of power supply from renewable sources by 2030.\n\nAnura Kumara Dissanayake's policies, on the other hand, emphasize the importance of transitioning to a green economy, addressing environmental sustainability and climate change challenges, and promoting international partnerships and investments in sustainable energy projects. His approach is more focused on empowering industries to meet global market standards and achieving long-term resilience and skill development in the industrial sector.\n\nOverall, both candidates prioritize environmental sustainability and renewable energy, but their approaches and focus areas differ. Ranil Wickremesinghe's policies are more focused on specific targets and timelines, while Anura Kumara Dissanayake's policies are more focused on empowering industries and promoting international partnerships."